üö®Alabama SOS Finds ERIC's DC Office EMPTY!üö®

Alabama Secretary of State Wes Allen made an unannounced visit to the published address of the headquarters of the Electronic Registration Information Center (ERIC) this month, but found no ERIC headquarters at the location.

"As his first official act in office, Allen withdrew the state from the voting registration system, keeping a promise he made on the campaign trail.

‚ÄúI was in D.C. for a meeting of the National Association of Secretaries of States and, since I was in town, I went to see the ERIC Headquarters,‚Äù Allen said. ‚ÄúWhat I found was that there was no ERIC headquarters at that address. There were no employees. There were no servers. There was no ERIC presence of any kind.

‚ÄúInstead, I found a virtual office that is rentable by the day. What it was missing was people, servers and any sign of the ERIC team.‚Äù

ERIC‚Äôs published address is 1201 Connecticut Ave NW Ste 600 in Washington, DC., but Allen found that the location is actually operated by Expansive, a company that offers virtual workspaces across the country and rents space by the day."

https://yellowhammernews.com/secretary-of-state-eric-address-is-vacant/

BIG WIN for Election Integrity  - Kenosha School Board Reinstates Member Eric Meadows

I want to thank Brian Thomas of Kenosha who is an ongoing supporting member of the WVA.  Brian notified us of a school board member Eric Meadows who was arbitrarily ousted from the school board in the Kenosha Unified School District (KUSD). 
 
Eric Meadows had been elected for a three year term and now was being ousted after a year.  The reason KUSD made this decision was because of a "clerical" error.  The board seat Meadows ran for was a three year term. However, after the fact KUSD said it was supposed to be for one year.  

This appeared to WVA to be an election issue and the WVA immediately brought this to the attention of Erick Kaardal, the Thomas More Society (TMS) lawyer we‚Äôve worked with from our beginning.

After a few calls, it was determined that, indeed, without any legal stance whatsoever, KUSD had made the decision to oust Eric Meadows from the board where he had been elected to fill a 3 year term.  So, a cease-and-desist letter was sent to the school board.

Following their receipt of the letter, the school board had an open school board meeting at which time they announced that indeed Eric Meadows was being ousted from the board.  It should be noted Mr. Meadows is one of two conservatives on a board of seven.  At that meeting a number of supporters of Meadows were carrying signs that bore the name of Eric Meadows.  The school board walked out and shut down the meeting because, in their eyes, the signs of Eric Meadows were ‚Äúadvertising/promotion‚Äù, and it is not allowed in accordance with their rule 1510 Advertising/Promotion (attached).

This is really interesting because at the same time these signs with Eric‚Äôs name on them is being considered as advertising/promotion, this same school board is allowing LGBTQA+ and BLM flags to be flown and they are not advertising/promotion, also, at most board meetings, teachers‚Äô union members show up wearing T-shirts with the big red fist.  Methinks this is way odd!

At that Monday, Feb 20th meeting after the rhubarb concerning the advertising/promotion topic, the board decided to hold a virtual meeting to take up this subject.  Talk about weak, this board leadership doesn't have the backbone of a jellyfish. On Thursday evening Feb 23rd, the board decided to keep Eric Meadows on for another year.  This occurred only after Erick Meadows and TMS lawyer had appeared on Fox and Friends that morning to let the world know how the KUSD was acting outside of the law.   Morning Feb 23 Fox News   --   https://www.foxnews.com/video/6321027107112  Fox news had them on again after the board decided it was in their interest to keep Meadows on the board.  Here is that clip
https://www.foxnews.com/video/6321120331112

I opened this update thanking Brian Thomas, a WVA member and supporter.  It was because Brian was involved and called WVA with the problem initially that TMS was able to intervene and get justice for Eric Meadows.  I extend to every member, if you have any kinds of issues similar to this going on in your community, let us know ASAP.  The WVA is proud to have assisted in this case.

BTW the KUSD is not off the hook yet, there are lingering issues to be taken care of like the LGBTQIA+ and BLM flags displayed at the schools and union T-shirts being worn in board meetings.  And, should Eric Meadows get the 3 year term he was elected for?
 
Ron Heuer 
President, WVA

A few words on the new Twitter ban that is currently in place for myself, Patriotic Alternative and several other groups.

Twitter - despite Musk's take over is not really a hub for free speech, and since Musk's take over the following groups/people have remained banned or have been banned after being reinstated:

Myself, Laura Towler and Patriotic Alternative (plus associated accounts)
Mike Enoch, Eric Striker and the National Justice Party (plus associated accounts)
Nick Fuentes and America First (plus associated accounts)
Jared Taylor and American Renaissance
Paul Golding and Britain First (plus associated accounts)
Tommy Robinson

There are probably others too that I have missed ‚Äì and if I have missed you off this list, send me a message and I will add you.

But what do all these people and organisations have in common? Well, the common thread between them all is that they all are active in the real world, and they all arrange real life events, take part in real life protests and call for people to something more than simply watch content online that they agree with. They are not simply talking heads or people looking to make the next hot take - they take action.

Now all of the above-mentioned people and groups wouldn‚Äôt agree with each other on everything. But they would all agree on trying to get people out doing political activity in real life. And that is the one thing the system fears the most ‚Äì real people, organising in the real world to create real change in order to take back power from the anti-white establishment.

My evening research project: 

Feel free to add to the list from 2022.
_____
PACs and individuals associated with the rail industry donated $3,190,763 (https://www.opensecrets.org/political-action-committees-pacs/industry-detail/M04/2022) in total to political candidates in 2021-22. This data comes from OpenSecrets, a non-profit organization that tracks the impact of money on American politics. Of this tota
l, $1,764,695 was given to Republican candidates, $1,408,068 to their Democratic rivals. Rep Sam Graves - MO, Sen Jerry Moran (R-KS), Sen Eric Schmitt (R - MO), Sen John Thune (R-SD), and Rep Earl Blumenauer (D-OR).
__
Media tries to normalize the quantities of train derailments. These costs passed onto consumers. Where is congress on infrastructure? 
__
Checking derailment dates, location, causes, action remedy; any patterns? Many derailments this year are "still under investigation." Department of Transportation‚Äôs Bureau of Transportation Statistics‚Äô show thousands more of trucks carry twice as much hazardous material than trains. Anyone care to do the timeline research?
___
1/9/2023 - Lake City, SC. Struck a vehicle on tracks. Derailment caused a water main break and advisory issued to citizens to boil their water. Train cars removed.

1/11/2023 - Feather River Canyon, CA. Load grain. Plumas County District 2 Supervisor, Kevin Goss, stated a landslide caused derailment. Unknown when derailed cars will be removed. 

1/17/2023 - Girdwood, AK Caused by avalanche. Load, freight, 6,091 tons. Alaska Department of Transportation and Public Facilities, told the Anchorage Daily News that the debris spread about 300 feet across the tracks and was about 30 feet deep.

1/19/2023 - Between Trinway & Adam's Mill, Ohio. Load, empty. Train cars removed. 

1/21/2023 - Loris, SC. Load rocks & gravel. Cars uprighted. 

1/27/2023 - Keatchie, LA. Load corrosive acid. Union Pacific, said two rail cars spilled propinoic acid, which is used as a preservative, fungicide, and antimicrobial agent, and acetic anhydride, which is used in making plastics, drugs, dyes, perfumes, explosives and aspirin. Officials say 10,000 gallons of Acetic Anhydride and less than 1,000 gallons of Propionic spilled. Citizens evacuated with 1.5 miles; returned home on 1/29/2023. The Caddo Parish Sheriff‚Äôs Office (CPSO) noted on Facebook that the derailment also caused the closure of the southbound lane of Louisiana Highway 789 at Keithville-Keatchie Road.

2/1/2023 - Detroit, MI & Talladega County, AL. According to the Talladega County Emergency Management Agency, one of the cars was leaking limestone slurry. 

2/3/2023 - E. Palestine, OH. Load contained including¬†vinyl chloride, butyl acrylate, ethylene 
glycol monobutyl ether, ethylhexyl acrylate and isobutylene ‚Äì all materials that are¬†widely considered to be toxic. The 141-car derailed train was also carrying several other hazardous and flammable substances such as isobutylene, butyl acrylate, ethylhexyl acrylate and ethylene glycol monobutyl ether. 2/17/2023 Early next week, the state plans to open a medical clinic in the village to evaluate those who are worried and analyze their symptoms, Ohio Gov. Mike DeWine announced. The clinic will include a team of experts in chemical exposures that is being deployed to eastern Ohio. 2/21/2023 Crews are still working to respond to the freight disaster. NTSB reported 2/23/2023 that cause was overheated wheel bearing and defected detector [AKA hot boxes] in rail.

2/4/2023 - Philadelphia, PA - passenger cars. Officials said the incident happened as a result of a broken piece of track. Broken track repaired. 

2/10/2023 - Toledo, OR. Load diesel. Absorbent boom, contaminated soil 16,000 tons hauled away to local landfill & fresh landfill put in place. Tracks repaired. 

2/13/2023 - Enoree, SC; Montgomery, TX; Splendora, TX [these 2 different towns appeared in news but sounds like the same incident]. In Montgomery, the train hit a truck. Load some hazardous materials - Union Pacific monitors air quality at the site.
